SUMMARY:TWiV 1332: Clinical update with Dr. Daniel Griffin
DTSTART:20260620T040000Z
DTEND:20260620T050000Z
DTSTAMP:20260624T071233Z
UID:2bda9fc39f72a409@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Podcast - TWiV
DESCRIPTION:[Podcast: This Week in Virology]\n\nIn his weekly clinical upd
 ate\, Daniel Griffin and Vincent Racaniello express concern &nbsp\;about v
 accine policy and ACIP\, scaling back of the CDC’s role in global public
  health\, shingles vaccine and dementia\, new screwworm cases\, the Ebola 
 outbreak in the Congo and Uganda and where the hantavirus outbreak began\,
  before Dr. Griffin deep dives into the measles outbreak\, recent statisti
 cs on RSV\, influenza and SARS-CoV-2 infections\, the Wasterwater Scan das
 hboard\, Johns Hopkins measles tracker\, Virgina outbreak of measles\, how
  to access and pay for Paxlovid\, how more people were negatively impacted
  by influenza than COVID\, discontinuing contact precautions for COVID\, w
 here to go for answers about long COVID-19\, and contacting your federal g
 overnment representative to stop the assault on science and biomedical res
 earch. Click arrow to play Download&nbsp\; TWiV 1332 (33 MB .mp3\, 54 min)
  Subscribe (free):&nbsp\; Apple Podcasts \, RSS \,&nbsp\; email Become a&n
 bsp\; patron &nbsp\;of&nbsp\;TWiV! Links for this episode Today we filed a
  motion asking the First Circuit to expedite our appeal of the district co
 urt&#8217\;s order in the AAP lawsuit that left ACIP—the nation&#8217\;s
  vaccine advisory committee—without a quorum (X) 4:01 CDC advisers drop 
 decades-old universal hepatitis B birth dose recommendation\, suggest bloo
 d testing after 1 dose (CIDRAP) HHS asks for expedited appeal of court rul
 ing on US vaccine policy (CIDRAP) 4:01 New Plan Scales Back C.D.C.’s Wor
 k on Diseases Abroad (NY Times)\n\nEvent URL: https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/
 twiv-1332/\n\nSource: twiv_podcast
LOCATION:Podcast
URL:https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1332/
